text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra Maven dependency or Docker service is needed for meaningful Vert.x Web Client coverage; tests can use an in-process Vert.x HTTP server. However io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1 resolves Vert.x Core 5.0.1 with Netty 4.2.2.Final, matching the existing 5.0.0 Netty 4.2.x native-run workaround, so the generated fix should preserve/apply the native runtime system properties for 5.0.1.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For native-image runs on JDK 25/current-defaults, set runtime system properties for the generated test binary: -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true. The existing 5.0.0 test scaffold applies these only when libraryVersion == '5.0.0'; extend the condition or otherwise apply them for 5.0.1 as well. Meaningful tests can run entirely against a local Vert.x HttpServer on 127.0.0.1 and should not require external network services.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The public OAuth2WebClient API references the optional io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2 module; only add that dependency if tests intentionally exercise OAuth2WebClient, because core WebClient/session/cache/form coverage does not require it.\",\n    \"Local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative for whether the Netty/JDK25 runtime properties are sufficient.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0d58a0a0d914bb4a016a417dcbffe88190a0a402d5dc0fda3e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 546, "output": 1327, "cacheRead": 37376, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 39249, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782676922820, "responseId": "resp_0d58a0a0d914bb4a016a417dbb8b7c8190aa8cb5ba72409f96"}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering dependencies for coverage**\n\nI'm wondering if optional dependencies are really \"concrete evidence of extra setup needed.\" It seems they aren't necessary for meaningful coverage. Existing tests currently avoid OAuth2, but for OAuth2WebClient, I think we might need an extra dependency since it's part of the artifact's public API. \n\nHmm, I need to decide if the library needs more than the usual generated test scaffold. It sounds like the necessary setup relates to runtime arguments before a native run can pass, especially regarding system properties.\n\n**Ensuring valid JSON structure**\n\nI'm considering the need for an \"action,\" specifically `advisory_preparation`, if the agent guidance isn't empty. It seems like I need to be strict about having a single valid JSON structure. I want to ensure everything is in order and that there’s no room for confusion. Making sure it’s deterministic and that the JSON isn't empty is key here. I'll double-check all details to achieve the right format!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0d58a0a0d914bb4a016a417dbc22f08190b4c6a81a1c439824\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQX3MFhG_SKghqzJEB56-mo7vqaNQ1oeOiZILMQDXtKhMh0KaLdd8zHFBxJR5ropluWwpZiqU5Qa494FFmf6lB1JsOOyIxnuK_8FDYCFKz8FLSjM7IjMOEAwzc4R5xJeQAT6aTmLzXJK-XwKgLLKr3lJRO-RbGcN5w_k11nIhA4IY-stO7p2fdOBTVY4NfzwZqM12545hmLcixcfNpCrQKCg5cyHWfRRkud9pSsM-WYcR-EPxzPb3j1CWWAlQtJ3-ZfbnRtctR7B03oI72DTURiJFor3I8TqC5Wc95aRW2BsXmkOVCwF5cDf6EZXMQMKb08QYLSLHw7suNlSnvYe5znSMSoQoCB1-fbGL3YoqbXGh_lEyJ7AW3D30xnA7l9C8VZONrLhBGDcY8eJbe5d5YUe68dUNdZPpWwS28GYSnqFelblgsv-19VG9Hu72kJSEjfab-Ywrj5G1OsGtOT0dSa3davmOytM5kjORAt2ZzIn5NgtEwuB5zgLp51xZmtpLCThL5IHC0iHvlehRwOxu1KxpejBUSBEolB98MKQX7YRaifrditMNY6niC53o4csT6c1Q2unCTbUwfQbzHsgJMCSIjlAw_6_vq4KKpVqEPGuexKHnocPcRtbKcfJ9ShNDDsoz0QRF35fJAYJSbH_6zX-hN5qpQ2fb4hvDTRf7D0oxUMqfDdax2G0YEtYrlhKgRp2ii_ts