t": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra Maven dependency or Docker service is needed for meaningful Vert.x Web Client coverage; tests can use an in-process Vert.x HTTP server. However io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1 resolves Vert.x Core 5.0.1 with Netty 4.2.2.Final, matching the existing 5.0.0 Netty 4.2.x native-run workaround, so the generated fix should preserve/apply the native runtime system properties for 5.0.1.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For native-image runs on JDK 25/current-defaults, set runtime system properties for the generated test binary: -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true. The existing 5.0.0 test scaffold applies these only when libraryVersion == '5.0.0'; extend the condition or otherwise apply them for 5.0.1 as well. Meaningful tests can run entirely against a local Vert.x HttpServer on 127.0.0.1 and should not require external network services.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The public OAuth2WebClient API references the optional io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2 module; only add that dependency if tests intentionally exercise OAuth2WebClient, because core WebClient/session/cache/form coverage does not require it.\",\n    \"Local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative for whether the Netty/JDK25 runtime properties are sufficient.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0d58a0a0d914bb4a016a417dcbffe88190a0a402d5dc0fda3e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 546, "output": 1327, "cacheRead": 37376, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 39249, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782676922820, "responseId": "resp_0d58a0a0d914bb4a016a417dbb8b7c8190aa8cb5ba72409f96"}, "toolResults": []}
